As history confirms, people will change their minds about almost anything, from which god they worship to how they style their hair. But when it comes to existential judgments, human beings in general
have an unfalteringly good opinion of themselves and their condition in
this world and are steadfastly confident they are not a collection of selfconscious nothings.
